article.headline: Lehigh 96, SW Arthmore 33
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 17 points and four other Lehigh players were in double figures as Lehigh dominated Swarthmore 96-33 on Wednesday night. Greg Page had 12 points and 10 rebounds for Lehigh (3-6) while Zahir Carrington also scored 12 points, Matt Szalachowski added 11 points and Jason Mgebroff contributed 10. Dillon McGrew scored eight points to lead Swarthmore (1-4), which trailed 45-19 at the half. The Mountain Hawks held a 53-21 rebounding advantage and forced 19 turnovers by Swarthmore, which shot just 12-of-55 from the field.
